description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CAMHS Paediatric Mental Health Nurse Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within our Paediatric department for a 1 year fixed term Band 6 CAMHS Nurse.  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Paediatric team at the Royal Surrey are looking for a dedicated and experienced childrens mental health nurse to work alongside our existing paediatric mental health and safeguarding teams. You will work within the ward area, childrens out patients and the emergency department when providing care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an individual who will support risk assessment and care planning for these children in the acute environment. To work effectively as part of the wider multi agency team to ensure that children and their families are well supported and enabled to move on from the acute environment in a timely manner with safe care plans in place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be an excellent communicator and willing to work alongside the childrens nursing and medical teams in the ward environment. In addition you will be willing to support with developing the team through training in your specialist area of care. We are looking for someone who is willing to work flexibly and will complement the skill set in our existing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information please contact Senal Soyer Paediatric Matron 01483 571122 ext. 2044 s.soyer@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
